		<div id="comment_body_64454354"><p><i>The Citizens United majority opinion makes no reference to corporate personhood or the Fourteenth Amendment, but rather argues that political speech rights do not depend on the identity of the speaker, which could be a person or an association of people</i></p><p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Corporate_personhood#:~:text=The%20Citizens%20United%20majority%20opinion,or%20an%20association%20of%20people" title="wikipedia.org">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/...</a> [wikipedia.org].</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64454354">

